Package org.eclipse.swt.custom

Class StyleRange

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.swt.graphics.TextStyle
org.eclipse.swt.custom.StyleRange
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class StyleRange
extends TextStyle
implements java.lang.Cloneable
StyleRange defines a set of styles for a specified range of text.

The hashCode() method in this class uses the values of the public fields to compute the hash value. When storing instances of the class in hashed collections, do not modify these fields after the object has been inserted.

  • Field Details

    • start

      public int start
      the start offset of the range, zero-based from the document start

    • length

      public int length
      the length of the range

    • fontStyle

      public int fontStyle
      the font style of the range. It may be a combination of SWT.NORMAL, SWT.ITALIC or SWT.BOLD Note: the font style is not used if the font attribute is set
